narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you want to learn to read French in a semester. It's amazing how much you can pick up - at the end, you'll still be limited by your vocabulary and some of the finer points of tense and whatever, but it's a useful skill and the class isn't bad either (mostly grad students). Good for a 5th class/credit/d. Two or three tests, weekly homework, translation projects - overall, not too bad.
I would recommend it to someone who needs a reading knowledge and is ready to invest at least and hour a day reading. I feel it is more suitable to graduate students.
Yes, I would recommend the course to those who need to read French, as it accomplishes this aim.

An overall good class but with a large workload. Definitely recommended for students in need of French instruction for translation purposes, but I would take it during a semester when one's overall workload is lighter than usual.
